Bug.WithStack:
To produce this defect: - Create an adapter file with the temple log file attached. - Specify ## for the start pattern of the extractor and \n for its end pattern - Click on the 'rerun adapter' button - The log records are extracted and can be browsed - Now add the associatedEvents attribute to the CBE, save, and rerun the adapter again - Notice that the log records are not extracted any more - Deleting the associatedEvents attribute and running the adapter again should fix the problem. Created attachment 10855 Template Log File Problem is an incorrect name for the Associated Events attribute resolvedEvents in ICBEPropertyConstants.
The following value:
public static final String ASSOCIATEDEVENT_RESOLVEDEVENT = "resolvedEvent";
should be:
public static final String ASSOCIATEDEVENT_RESOLVEDEVENT = "resolvedEvents";
Because the attribute was not found the CBEFormatter class tries to log a message but this throws a null pointer exception. Here is the code:
CommonBaseEvent event = getEventFactory().createCommonBaseEvent();
event.getMsgDataElement().setMsgCatalogId ("HyadesGA_CBE_Formatter_Invalid_AssociatedEvent_WARN_");
event.getMsgDataElement().setMsgCatalogTokensAsStrings(new String[]{getUniqueID (),(String)path.get(4)});
event.setSeverity(CommonBaseEvent.SEVERITY_WARNING);
log(event);
event.getMsgDataElement() is null. Fixes for these problems:
Fixes: 1) fix the typo in org.eclipse.hyades.logging.adapter.ICBEPropertyConstants.ASSOCIATEDEVENT_RESOLVE DEVENT 2) Component.getEventFactory was fixed by adding a eventFactory.setCompleteEvent (true); call so that when the CBE is generated the template handler will be run to complete the initialization of the CBE. 3) Component.log(CommonBaseEvent event) was fixed by adding || msg.length() == 0 to the end of if(msg == null) This is necessary because the template handler sets the CBE msg to an empty string instead of null. This change will cause the msg attribute to be filled with the correct text based on msgCatalogId and msgCatalogTokens. 4) Added the following to the Component.clean() method to prevent a NullPointerException during Context cleanup. if (components == null) { return; } Committed to Head Verified fix with driver 3.0_20040528_1612

