Bug.WithStack:
This behavior is identical under both the "Default" profile and the "Java
Conventions" profile. I am working with I20040514.

Test case:

This formatting looks good:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
if (referencedObject == null
        || !(referencedObject instanceof IProjectDefinition)
        && !(referencedObject instanceof ProjectDefinitionDelegate)) {
    invalidReference();
} else {
    log("Using previously loaded project definition.",
            Project.MSG_DEBUG);
}

However if I add parens, it doesn't wrap properly. The entire second
part of the OR condition appears on a single line:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
if (referencedObject == null
		|| (!(referencedObject instanceof IProjectDefinition) && !(referencedObject
instanceof ProjectDefinitionDelegate))) {
	invalidReference();
} else {
	log("Using previously loaded project definition.",
			Project.MSG_DEBUG);
}
formatter (except for comments and auto-indentation) is core.
Reconsider post 3.0.
As of now 'LATER' and 'REMIND' resolutions are no longer supported.
Please reopen this bug if it is still valid for you.

